title: Static Analysis

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.CAMERA.description: Allows application to take pictures and videos with the camera. This allows the application to collect images that the camera is seeing at any time.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to external storage.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from external storage.

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO.description: Allows application to access the audio record path.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

manifest_analysis.title:
Application Data can be Backed up
[android:allowBackup] flag is missing.
manifest_analysis.desc: The flag [android:allowBackup] should be set to false. By default it is set to true and allows anyone to backup your application data via adb. It allows users who have enabled USB debugging to copy application data off of the device.
manifest_analysis.name: Application Data can be Backed up [android:allowBackup] flag is missing.

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.cloudmosa.app.LemonActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

manifest_analysis.title:
Broadcast Receiver (com.cloudmosa.app.ReferrerReceiver) is not Protected.
[android:exported=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: A Broadcast Receiver is found to be shared with other apps on the device therefore leaving it accessible to any other application on the device.
manifest_analysis.name: is not Protected. [android:exported=true]

nx.description: The shared object has NX bit set. This marks a memory page non-executable making attacker injected shellcode non-executable.

stack_canary.description: This shared object has a stack canary value added to the stack so that it will be overwritten by a stack buffer that overflows the return address. This allows detection of overflows by verifying the integrity of the canary before function return.

relocation_readonly.description: This shared object has full RELRO enabled. RELRO ensures that the GOT cannot be overwritten in vulnerable ELF binaries. In Full RELRO, the entire GOT (.got and .got.plt both) is marked as read-only.

rpath.description: The shared object does not have run-time search path or RPATH set.

runpath.description: The shared object does not have RUNPATH set.

fortify.description: The shared object does not have any fortified functions. Fortified functions provides buffer overflow checks against glibc's commons insecure functions like strcpy, gets etc. Use the compiler option -D_FORTIFY_SOURCE=2 to fortify functions.

metadata.description: The App logs information. Sensitive information should never be logged.
metadata.cwe: CWE-532 Insertion of Sensitive Information into Log File

metadata.description: App can read/write to External Storage. Any App can read data written to External Storage.
App uses SQLite Database and execute raw SQL query. Untrusted user input in raw SQL queries can cause SQL Injection. Also sensitive information should be encrypted and written to the database.
metadata.cwe: CWE-89 Improper Neutralization of Special Elements used in an SQL Command ('SQL Injection')
CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: SHA-1 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.

metadata.cwe: CWE-327 Use of a Broken or Risky Cryptographic Algorithm
metadata.description: MD5 is a weak hash known to have hash collisions.
This App uses SSL certificate pinning to detect or  prevent MITM attacks in secure communication channel.

metadata.cwe: CWE-312 Cleartext Storage of Sensitive Information
metadata.description: Files may contain hardcoded sensitive informations like usernames, passwords, keys etc.
The App uses an insecure Random Number Generator.
metadata.cwe: CWE-330 Use of Insufficiently Random Values

metadata.description: Insecure Implementation of SSL. Trusting all the certificates or accepting self signed certificates is a critical Security Hole. This application is vulnerable to MITM attacks
This App copies data to clipboard. Sensitive data should not be copied to clipboard as other applications can access it.

"sb_privacy_content3" : "－－－－－－－－－－－
CloudMosa プライバシーポリシー
 
このプライバシーポリシーは、CloudMosa（以下「当社」といいます。）が収集する可能性のあるお客様の情報およびお客様による本アプリの利用状況に関する情報の範囲、使用方法について説明するものです。 
なお、当社は予告無しに当社の裁量で本アプリとサービスのプライバシーポリシーを変更する場合があります。
 
お客様の情報について 
CloudMosaにユーザーアカウントはありません。これは個人情報管理に関しては、良い仕組みであると考えます。当社のシステムは、論理上は、ステートレスです。つまり、お客様が一度当社のアプリの使用を止め、サービスを退会すると、お客様の情報は一切当社の元には残らない仕組みになっています。当社は、ログデータを参照することにより、お客様のアクティビティにリンクすることはできますが、お客様のお名前、ご住所、メールアドレス、電話番号などの個人情報をたどることは不可能です。
 
お客様の利用状況に関する情報について 
当社は標準のウェブログと同様に、TCPレイヤー（ソースIP, ソースポート、デスティネーションIP、デスティネーションポート等）とHTTPレイヤーでお客様のアクティビティを記録します。一度ログサーバーから収集されると、ログはworker beeサーバーから消去されます。ログサーバーによってログの分析、レポートが作成され、その後ログが消去されます。そのレポートは統計データとして蓄積されますが、当社がレポートを参照しても、当社が個人のユーザーを特定することは不可能です。
 
収集した情報の使用方法 
ログはトラブルシューティングと自己防衛のために使われます。レポートは、ビジネスインテリジェンスのために使われます。しかし、過度の量のログとレポートを維持して管理するには、費用がかかります。当社は、ログはたびたび消去し、レポートは永久に保存します。ログは内部でしか利用されることはなく、レポートは、資金調達などのため、しばしば外部で利用されることもあります。 
当社は、収集したログを、トラブルシューティングと自己防衛のために使用します。当社は、収集したログを、当社の内部でのみ使用するものとし、当社の判断によって定期的に消去します。当社は、収集したレポートを、ビジネスインテリジェンスのために使用します。当社は、収集したレポートを、期間の定めなく保存するものとし、資金調達などの目的のため、当社の外部でも使用することがあります。
 
ページコンテンツの記録に関して 
ウェブページのURLが記録されていたとしても、ウェブページのコンテンツは記録されていません。ウェブページのコンテンツ自体が記録されることはなく、本規約は厳密に施行されます。しかし、諜報機関の監査には、十分注意してください。
 
最終更新日　2013年12月3日"

playstore_details.title: Puffin Web Browser
playstore_details.description:
Puffin Web Browser is wicked fast. Once users experience the thrilling speed of Puffin, regular Mobile Internet feels like torture. For light users, it is ad-sponsored. For heavy users, it requires subscription through In-App-Purchase.

🚀 Wicked Fast: Puffin speeds up mobile browsing by shifting the workload from the resource-limited devices to the cloud servers, and resource-demanding webpages can run super-fast on your phones or tablets.

🔒 Cloud Protection: All traffic from Puffin app to Puffin server are encrypted, a protection from nearby hackers. It’s safe to use public non-secure WiFi through Puffin, but not safe at all for most browsers. 

🎥 Flash Support: Web browser sessions are protected by Puffin Cloud Isolation, and Adobe Flash player is supported over the cloud safely.

💰 Data Savings: Puffin uses proprietary compression algorithm to transmit web data to your device, and it can save up to 90% of your bandwidth on regular web browsing. (Please be noted that streaming Flash content or videos requires more bandwidth than the normal usage.)

Features:
☆ Incredible page load and rendering speed
☆ Adobe Flash support over cloud during the daytime (also works on Android 4.4+)
☆ Download to cloud (up to 1G per file)
☆ Theater mode for Flash videos and games
☆ Virtual trackpad and gamepad
☆ Color theme for toolbar and sidebar 
☆ Fastest JavaScript engine
☆ Full web experience (desktop and mobile view）
☆ Incognito tab: Auto-clean your browsing activities in the app

===== Limitations =====
* The data centers of Puffin Web Browser are in the US and the cloud servers can only access public web sites from US geolocations. 
* For users outside the US, local contents, especially videos of local interest, may not be accessible from the US due to geo-restrictions in their home countries.
* Puffin is blocked in some countries (e.g., China, Saudi Arabia, United Arab Emirates) and by some schools (e.g., in United States).

For more information, please check our FAQ: https://www.puffinbrowser.com/help/
